dc:source  a    owl:AnnotationProperty .

gomodel:SYNGO_5444  a     owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Rationale: \"KIF3, a member of the kinesin-2 family, forms a heterotrimeric complex that consists of KIF3A, KIF3B, and kinesin-associated protein 3 (KAP3) (Kondo et al., 1994, Teng et al., 2005, Yamazaki et al., 1996).\"\n\nAuthors show that KIF3A is involved in the transport of N-cadherin (Cadherin-2, gene CDH2), a synaptic adhesion molecule, to dendritic spines.\n\nHighlights section;\n- The cargo-bound KIF3A was phosphorylated by specific kinases, PKA and CaMKIIa.\n- Phosphorylation of the KIF3A upregulates the loading and transport of N-cadherin.\n- N-cadherin was accumulating in the spine during homeostatic plasticity.\n- Phospho-KIF3A enhances the N-cadherin accumulation during homeostatic plasticity.. Experimental description: M&M: \"Hippocampal and cortical cells were obtained from mouse brains on embryonic day 17.\"" ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
        dc:contributor    "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-4973-5732" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2286-1587" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2514-0216" ;
        dc:date           "2023-03-17" ;
        dc:title          "SYNGO_BP_5444" ;
        pav:providedBy    "https://syngo.vu.nl" ;
        biolink:in_taxon  "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/NCBITaxon_10090" .

